Request amount of $848,329 will cover essential expenses for successful implementation of this award activities, which are part of the following categories of the approved budget:
Salary and Wages (Income taxes charged under salaries) for collaborators performing life-saving activities		in total of $174,185;
Travel (Travel expenses to the districts and sites in Cabo Delgado for life-saving activities in internally displaced and vulnerable populations) in total of $7,905;
Contractual (District and Provincial Hospitals advances for life-saving activities and April salaries for outsourced lay site-level and community staff)	in total of $579,164 and 
Other (Trainings of lay counsellors, mentor mothers, and other health professionals in the Cabo Delgado districts) in total of	$87,075.

The CDC-RFA-DP22-2207 award focuses on growing Perinatal Quality Collaboratives (PQC) 's capacity to implement best healthcare practices for all pregnant mothers and their newborns. The funds we are requesting in our March invoice, reimburse us for: staff salaries, consultants, and contractors, etc; for work on planning and implementing a quality improvement project focused on postpartum hemorrhage reduction. Hemorrhage is one of the leading causes of maternal mortality in the United States. By proactively training healthcare providers to address this condition, we can save mothers' lives, ensuring babies grow up with healthy families. 

Timeframe 03/01/2025 – 03/31/2025

Staff Salaries Total: 5,204.09; 
Fringe Total: 1,291.76; 
Consulting Total: 8,600.00; 
Contract Total: 1,200.00; 
Other 3,778.93; 
Indirect (10%): 2,007.48; 
Total: 22,082.26. 

We paid our consultants: Strategic Corporate Solutions for work on our strategic plan and evaluation process, and our Quality Improvement Advisor, for her input on our Quality Improvement Initiatives.  We compensated our Marketing Support Contractor for her work on maintaining our website, and newsletter communications. Our Other expenses include costs for attending two conferences, and staff development.

The CDC-RFA-DP22-2207 supplement award focuses on growing the capacity of Perinatal Quality Collaboratives (PQC) to address substance use disorders during and after pregnancy. The funds we are requesting in our March invoice, reimburse us for costs relating to: staff salaries, consultants, and contractors, etc; for work on planning and implementing two quality improvement projects focused on resource sharing and naloxone training. Substance use during pregnancy is the leading cause of maternal mortality in Minnesota. By training healthcare providers to address this condition proactively, we can save lives, prevent harm, and bring economic prosperity to the United States long term. 

​​Timeframe 03/01/2025 – 03/31/2025

Staff Salaries Total: 2,415.78; 
Fringe Total: 572.28; 
Indirect (10%): 298,81; 
Total: 3,286.87.
